# LapyTrack — Backend

## Structure
- **Single file:** `server.py` (~1100 lines) — all routes, models, startup
- `requirements.txt` — fastapi, motor, uvicorn, bcrypt, PyJWT, qrcode
- `Dockerfile` — python:3.11-slim + ca-certificates; `CMD uvicorn server:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port ${PORT}`
- Root repo `Dockerfile` copies `backend/` for Render

## Config env vars
```python
MONGO_URL / MONGODB_URI
DB_NAME (default: krish_computer_db)
JWT_SECRET
FRONTEND_URL (default: https://lapy-track.vercel.app)
CORS_ORIGINS (comma-separated; credentials require explicit origins)
```

## Important patterns
- `enrich_device(doc)` — regenerates QR SVG with current `FRONTEND_URL` on every device read
- `generate_qr_svg(device_id)` → `{FRONTEND_URL}/job/{device_id}`
- CORS: `allow_credentials=True` with explicit origins (never `*` + credentials)
- Public routes (no auth): `GET /api/public/job/{device_id}`, `GET /api/public/files/{path}`
- Private files: `GET /api/files/{path}` — requires auth
- Photos saved to `uploads/` + `files` collection metadata

## Auth endpoints
- `GET /auth/setup-status` — `needs_setup`, `has_email`
- `POST /auth/setup` — requires shop_name, email, password (10+ chars), pin
- `POST /auth/login` — PIN
- `POST /auth/login-email` — email + password

## MongoDB collections
`app_config`, `users`, `devices`, `movements`, `customers`, `transactions`, `categories`, `brands`, `issue_categories`, `banks`, `files`, `counters`, `reminders`

## Startup (`@app.on_event("startup")`)
Creates indexes, seeds brands/categories/banks if empty. **Fails deploy if MongoDB unreachable.**

## Local `.env`
Copy from `.env.example`. Never commit `.env`.
